Castello Baronale was built in the 12th century by Pope Urban VIII's nephew Cardinal Barberini . 
  The property was used as a fortress by Napoleon Bonaparte between 1796 and 1800 . 
  The castle is situated just 31 miles from Rome and towers 3,280ft over sea level . 
  It includes nine en-suite bedrooms, a lavish ballroom, library, gym and theatre . 
 